      "message": "For export_shared_lib_headers, I think any libs depending libxml2 should also see the headers without including libandroidicu in their build rule. For example, it\u0027s useful when the library passes C struct or C++ object as argument in the API.\n\nI actually can\u0027t see the doc of exclude_shared_libs in go/android.bp. But I think vendor lib can\u0027t see  libandroidicu at all. I think it\u0027s related to the face that LIBXML_ICU_ENABLED is off in VNDK, and thus the dependency can be excluded for vendor.\n\nI don\u0027t know the effect when they are used in mix, but I just change from libicuuc to libandroidicu in this CL, not the rest of the build rule..",
